# 🎯 Key Takeaways

✅ Traditional programming works best when rules are known.

✅ Some real-world problems are too complex to solve using manually written rules.

✅ Machine Learning learns patterns from data instead of relying only on hardcoded instructions.

✅ Machine Learning complements software engineering—it does not replace it.

